enhanced_by.reason: Both methods generate HTML output for the element, with html() focusing on the inner HTML and outerHtml() including the element's tag.
text() extracts the text content of the element, which can be used to verify the content before generating the HTML.
html(String) sets the inner HTML of the element, which can be used to validate the output of html() by comparing the set HTML with the generated HTML.
outerHtml() can be used to compare the full HTML output including the element's tag with the inner HTML output of html().
